ce:section.ce:para:
In this study, we hypothesized that combining CNs, BiP, and CDs would yield a novel photocatalytic adsorbent, CCHBi, with enhanced adsorption and photocatalytic degradation of lignin. The micromorphology, chemical composition and optical properties of the synthesized CCHBi were investigated using scanning electron microscopy (SEM), Fourier-transform infrared spectrometry (FTIR), X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS), X-ray diffractometry (XRD), and UV–vis diffuse reflectance spectroscopy (UV–vis DRS). The adsorption and photocatalytic behaviors of CCHBi were examined, focusing on the effects of pH, initial concentration (C

                        0
                     ), and time (t). Additionally, the mechanism underlying the enhanced adsorption and photocatalytic degradation of lignin by CCHBi was investigated.
